
[1]galanga

   GALAN'GA, n. A plant, species of the Maranta or Indian Arrow-Root, so
   called because the root is used to extract the virus communicated by
   poisoned arrows. This plant has thick, knotty, creeping roots, crowned
   with long, broad, arundinaceous leaves, with stalks half a yard high,
   terminated by bunches of monopetalous, ringent flowers.
